Whisk together mascarpone, chives, thyme, flour, egg yolks and remaining Parmesan. Add taleggio. Season. Whisk egg whites to medium peaks then fold in. Distribute between prepared ramekins. Bake for 25-30 mins, until puffed and golden. Serve immediately.

title: coconut balls
directions: Gently heat chocolate and heavy cream over low heat for 3-4 mins, until melted and smooth. Let cool slightly then add desiccated coconut, almonds and chocolate bar. Chill for 2 hours, until almost firm.
Shape into 24 small balls then roll in shredded coconut. Chill for 30 mins then serve.

title: beet, apple and fennel salad with smoked trout
directions: Mix the beet strips with 2 tbsp of lemon juice and 2 tsp of sugar in a pan. Simmer in a little water for 10 minutes. In a bowl, drizzle the apples and pear with 2 tbsp lemon juice.
To make the dressing, mix the remaining lemon juice with the crushed mustard seeds, sour cream, stock, 2 tbsp chopped thyme and 1 tsp sugar in a bowl and season to taste.
Mix the beets with the fennel, smoked trout, apple and pear wedges and cheese on a plate. Serve drizzled with salad dressing and garnished with thyme.

title: creamy salmon spread
directions: Bring the wine and 1/2 cup water to a boil in a saucepan. Add the salmon and simmer for 6-8 minutes then remove the fish from the saucepan. When cool, break it into pieces.
Heat the oil in a pan and saute the carrots for 2-3 minutes. Add 2 tbsp lemon juice, season with salt and pepper then remove from the pan and cool.

Beat the butter until creamy then stir in the cream. Stir in the salmon along with the carrot and 3/4 of the chives. Season to taste with lemon juice, salt, pepper and paprika. Serve with a sprinkling of the remaining chives and toasted bread

title: crossword puzzle cookies
directions: Using an electric mixer, beat butter, sugar and vanilla in a small bowl until light and creamy. Add egg yolk, beating until well combined. Stir in sifted flour. Mix with hands to form dough. Divide dough into 2 portions, flattening each to form a rectangle. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill for 30-40 mins or until firm.

Preheat oven to 350°F. Line 2 large baking sheets with parchment paper. Roll dough between sheets of parchment paper to 1/8 inch thick. Using a small, sharp knife and a ruler, cut dough into 1 1/2 inch squares.
Place squares on prepared sheets. Bake for 10-12 mins or until golden brown. Cool on sheets for 5 mins, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.

Line a baking sheet with fresh parchment paper. Sift powdered sugar into a medium heatproof bowl and stir in 2 tbsp boiling water to make a runny icing. Dip cookies into icing, draining any excess. Place cookies on prepared baking sheet and set aside for 30 mins to set. Using writing icing, pipe letters on to cookies.

title: mango and papaya carpaccio with sesame mousse
directions: Toast sesame seeds in a dry frying pan until golden, remove and allow to cool. Arrange mango and papaya slices in a circle on 4 plates.
Whisk tahini and milk together until creamy. Beat cream and vanilla extract and gently stir in tahini and milk mixture. Spoon into a piping bag.
Pipe a rosette of sesame mousse in the center of each plate of carpaccio. Garnish with toasted sesame seeds and mint leaves and drizzle with maple syrup.

title: english breakfast buns
directions: Preheat broiler to high. Line a baking sheet with parchment. Slice tops from rolls, a quarter of the way down; reserve. Scoop out centers and set aside. Heat oil in a small frying pan on high heat. Cook bacon for 1 min each side or until crisp.
Meanwhile, place beans and tomatoes in a medium microwave-safe bowl. Cook on high (100%) for 1 min or until bubbling, stirring once.
Line each roll with 2 pieces bacon. Pour hot bean mixture evenly into rolls. Crack 1 egg into each. Cook, one at a time, in the microwave on high (100%) for 45 seconds.

Arrange on tray. Broil for 2 mins. Sprinkle cheese over cut side of roll tops. Place on tray with rolls and broil for an additional 2 mins or until egg is set and cheese is melted. Serve rolls sprinkled with parsley. Use the cheesy lids for dipping.

title: spicy white fish with rice and guacamole
directions: Cook rice in boiling salted water for 12 mins, or until tender. Drain. Combine with corn, pepper and cilantro. Season.
Sprinkle both sides of fish with seasoning. Heat oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Cook fish for 2-3 mins per side, or until cooked to your liking.
Meanwhile, to make the guacamole, mash avocados until almost smooth. Add lemon juice and cilantro. Season.
Distribute rice between serving plates. Top with fish, guacamole and cilantro leaves. Serve with lime slices.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F.

Heat the oil in a frying pan and saute the onion until it's translucent. Add the chopped mushroom stems and season to taste. Stir in the sausage, mustard and thyme. Fill the mushrooms with the sausage mixture, place them in a baking dish and sprinkle them with grated cheese. Spread the diced tomatoes around the mushrooms and pour in the stock. Bake them for about 20 mins. Serve sprinkled with extra thyme.

title: crab cakes
directions: Cook potatoes in lightly salted boiling water for 15-20 mins, until tender. Drain then mash with butter and cream until smooth. Let cool. Add crab meat, lemon juice and chives. Season. Shape into 8 - 1 inch thick patties. Cover with plastic wrap and chill for 30 mins.

Dredge crab cakes in flour, shaking off excess. Dip in beaten egg then coat in breadcrumbs. Heat 1 inch oil in a deep frying pan. Working in batches, fry crab cakes for 6-7 mins, until golden and crisp on both sides. Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot with crispy potato wedges, salad and garlic mayonnaise.

title: grilled chicken tenders with spicy peach relish
directions: Heat an oiled grill pan on high heat or preheat the grill to medium-high. Cook chicken tenders for 5-10 mins, turning, until cooked through. Season to taste.
Meanwhile, heat oil in a large skillet on medium heat. Saute onion for 2-3 mins until tender. Add chili pepper and cook for 1 min until fragrant.
Stir in vinegar and sugar. Cook, stirring, until sugar dissolves. Mix in peaches and raisins. Cook, stirring, for a further 2-3 mins, until heated through.
Arrange salad greens on serving plates. Top with chicken and peach relish.

title: butter chicken and raita
directions: Combine chicken, 1/4 cup of the yogurt and tandoori paste in a shallow dish. Mix well. Cover; refrigerate 2 hours.
Melt 3 tbsp of the butter in a large, deep skillet on medium heat. Cook chicken 6-8 mins, turning, until browned all over. Remove and set aside.
Heat remaining 3 tbsp butter in same pan. Saute onion 4-5 mins, until lightly golden. Add chili pepper, ginger, garam masala, cumin and paprika. Cook, stirring, 1- 2 mins, until fragrant.
Return chicken to pan with tomato puree; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer 5-10 mins, until sauce thickens.
Meanwhile, for the raita, mix all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Stir remaining 1/2 cup yogurt and spinach into the skillet; heat gently. Serve chicken on a bed of rice, garnished with cilantro. Accompany with raita.

title: steak fajitas
directions: In a bowl, mix the chili powder, cumin, cayenne pepper, lemon juice and 6 tbsp oil. Stir in the cilantro, oregano, red onion and garlic. Coat the steak in the marinade and allow to marinate for 2 hours in the refrigerator.

Preheat the oven to 400°F. Remove the steak from the marinade and drain. Heat 2 tbsp oil in a frying pan and fry until browned all over. Add the white onion and peppers and cook for 5 mins. Add 4 tbsp marinade and bring to a boil. Season with salt and black pepper and remove from heat.

Heat the tortillas in the oven for 1-2 mins, until warmed through. Melt the butter and brush over tortillas. Spoon the steak mixture along the centers of the tortillas and roll up. Arrange in a shallow baking dish and spoon the creme fraiche in blobs all over. Sprinkle over the cheese.
Bake for 15 mins. Serve garnished with cilantro and chilies.

title: creamy chicken casserole with bread rolls
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Put the chicken filets in a pan, cover with the stock and simmer for 25 mins. Remove the chicken and set aside, then pass the cooking liquid through a strainer and reserve.

Dust the mushrooms with the flour. Melt the butter or margarine in a pan, and saute the mushrooms. Gradually stir in the reserved cooking liquid and the cream. Add the carrots and simmer for 5 mins. Cut the cooked chicken into cubes and add to the mixture along with the frozen peas. Cook for a further 5 mins, stirring all the time. Add the lemon juice to taste, and season. Put the mixture in an ovenproof dish (about 8-inches in diameter).

Cut the bread rolls in half horizontally and place at even intervals on top of the casserole in a single layer. Brush the rolls with the beaten egg and sprinkle with cheese. Bake in the oven for 15-20 mins and serve.

title: parmesan, tomato and olive tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 300°F. Place tomatoes, cut-side up, on a baking tray. Drizzle with 1 tbsp oil, sprinkle with 1 tsp thyme and season. Bake for 1 hour 10 mins, or until soft and starting to burst. Let cool.

Meanwhile, in a food processor, combine flour, cheese, butter and a pinch of salt. Pulse until combined. Add egg yolk and about 1 tbsp ice water and pulse until just combined. Knead gently on a lightly floured surface until smooth. Cover and chill for 30 mins.

Preheat oven to 350°F. Lightly grease a baking tray. Divide dough into 6 pieces. Roll each piece until about 1/8 inch thick. Cut into 4 inch rounds, place on prepared tray and chill for 30 mins. Bake for 20 mins, or until crisp and lightly browned. Let cool slightly.
Just before serving, top pastry rounds with tomatoes and olives. Drizzle with remaining oil and sprinkle with remaining thyme. Season.

title: loch ness panini (for kids)
directions: Cut the middles from the cheese slices, and cut 4 small circles of cheese and 4 even smaller circles of cucumber.

Cut the bagels in half horizontally and spread the cut sides with dressing. Layer the bottom halves of the bagels with 1 slice of cheese, 2 slices of beef and another slice of cheese. Put on the top half of the bagels and lightly coat both sides with olive oil cooking spray. On a preheated grill pan, grill each side for 2 mins, pressing down with a spatula. Cut the bagels in half and arrange the pepper and cucumber wedges in an alternating pattern radiating out from the filling. Arrange the bagel sections on plates to resemble the Loch Ness Monster. Lightly brush a little of the dressing onto the head sections and stick on the a circle of cheese and a circle of cucumber for the eyes. Serve immediately.

title: potato, bacon and apple skewers with lemon dip
directions: Cook the potatoes in salted boiling water for 15-20 mins until just tender. Drain. Set aside to cool.
For the lemon dip, mix the creme fraiche, lemon peel and sugar. Season to taste with salt and freshly ground black pepper.
For the marinade, mix the honey with 1 tbsp water and the red pepper flakes. Set aside.
Thread the potatoes onto 8 metal (or pre-soaked wooden) skewers with the apple, bacon, sage and onion. Brush with some of the marinade.
Heat a greased nonstick grill pan. Grill the skewers for 8-10 mins, turning occasionally and brushing several times with the marinade. Serve with the lemon dip.

title: buttermilk waffles with lemon sorbet
directions: Melt butter in a small saucepan and leave to cool. Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Whisk together buttermilk and eggs and stir into the dry ingredients and mix into a smooth, thin batter. Stir in melted butter and vanilla.
Grease the waffle maker with the sunflower oil and preheat it. Cook each waffle for 5 mins. Make approximately 10 waffles (4 x 4 inch) .
Arrange 2 waffles on each plate with 1 scoop of sorbet. Scatter with raspberries. Garnish with lemon zest, mint leaves and a dusting of powdered sugar.

title: harissa and mint vegetable stew
directions: Heat butter in a large saucepan over medium heat. Cook shallots and garlic, stirring, until shallots have softened. Add flour and cook, stirring, for 1 min. Add stock, potatoes, tomatoes, harissa, cinnamon and 2/3 of the mint. Add 2 cups water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 30 mins.
Add squash and simmer for 20 mins. Add corn, peas and cherry tomatoes. Simmer for 10 mins. Season to taste. Serve stew sprinkled with remaining mint.

title: chocolate and caramel lava cakes
directions: To make the caramel sauce, place sugar in a small saucepan. Cook over low heat, without stirring, for 8 mins, or until caramelized. Carefully add butter, cream and salt. Simmer for 2 mins, stirring if necessary, until smooth. Let cool to room temperature.
Preheat oven to 400°F. Grease 4 (11 oz) ramekins and place on a baking tray lined with parchment paper. Spoon 1 tbsp caramel sauce into each ramekin.

In a food processor, combine sugar, butter, flour, ground almonds, 2 tbsp cocoa powder, milk, eggs and vanilla and process until smooth. Transfer mixture to a large bowl and stir in chocolate. Distribute between ramekins.

Combine brown sugar and remaining cocoa powder in a small bowl. Sprinkle evenly over ramekins. Add 1/4 cup boiling water to each ramekin to wet the sugar. Bake for 25 mins, or until tops are firm to the touch.
Dust with cocoa powder. Serve immediately with ice cream and drizzled with remaining caramel sauce.

title: daisy cupcakes
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Line 8 cups of 12-cup muffin pan with paper liners.

Beat butter, vanilla extract, sugar, eggs, sifted flour and milk in large bowl with electric mixer on low speed until ingredients are combined. Increase speed to medium; beat until light and fluffy. Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake about 20 mins until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pan 5 mins. Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.

For the fluffy frosting, combine sugar and 2 tbsp water in a small saucepan. Stir on medium heat, without boiling, until sugar is dissolved. Boil, without stirring, for about 5 mins or until syrup reaches 241°F on a candy thermometer. Syrup should be thick but not colored. Remove from heat; allow bubbles to subside. Beat egg white in medium bowl with electric mixer until soft peaks form. While motor is operating, add hot syrup in a thin steady stream. Beat on high speed about 10 mins or until mixture is thick.
Spread cooled cupcakes with frosting. Use six mints to make the petals for each daisy, pushing gently into the frosting. Position sugar flowers in the center of each daisy.

title: green curaçao cocktail
directions: Mix together the Blue Curacao, lemon juice, orange juice and sugar syrup. Place the crushed ice in a 5 oz glass and pour in the drink mixture. Decorate with a lemon slice and serve.

title: pasta with mushroom ragout and spinach
directions: Heat butter and oil in a medium frying pan over high heat. Saute mushrooms and garlic for 3 mins. Reduce heat to low. Add chicken stock. Simmer, covered, for 5 mins. Remove lid. Increase heat to medium and add cream and thyme. Simmer for 5 mins, until reduced slightly. Mix in spinach.
Meanwhile, cook pasta in boiling, salted water until al dente. Drain. Toss with mushroom sauce. Season.
Serve topped with shaved Parmesan.

title: butterscotch raisin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease an 8 inch ring pan.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in honey then eggs, 1 at a time. Stir in raisins then flour and milk. Transfer to prepared pan.

To make the topping, combine flour and sugar in a bowl. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse breadcrumbs then stir in walnuts. Sprinkle over cake and bake for 45 mins. Let cool in pan for 5 mins then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.

title: rose cupcakes
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°F. Line 14 cups of a muffin pan with paper liners. Mix flour, baking powder and baking soda in a medium bowl.

Beat butter and sugar in a large bowl with electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add egg and egg whites, one at a time, beating well each addition. Fold in flour mixture alternately with yogurt. Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake for 15-20 mins, until well risen, golden and a toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pan 5 mins. Remove from pan; cool completely on a wire rack.

Meanwhile, for the rose icing, combine powdered sugar, rosewater, a few drops of food color and 1 tbsp hot water. Stir until smooth and shiny. Frost cupcakes and decorate with frosted rose petals, if desired.

For the frosted rose petals, whisk an egg white until foamy and brush onto rose petals (make sure they are unsprayed and safe to eat). Place petals on paper towel and dust with granulated sugar. Set aside to dry in the sun, if possible. Store in an airtight container.

title: coffee sauce
directions: Combine heavy cream and coffee in a small saucepan. Stir over medium heat, without boiling, until hot. Remove from heat. Add chocolate and whisk until smooth. Stir in liqueur.
Transfer to a small bowl, cover and chill for 15 mins, stirring occasionally.

title: lamb chops with mediterranean vegetables
directions: Heat 4 tbsp oil in a pot and saute the onions, eggplant, zucchini and tomatoes over high heat for 5 mins. Stir in the vinegar and season. Add the rosemary, bay leaves, wine and stock and simmer for 15 mins.

Meanwhile, heat 2 tbsp oil in a pan and sear the lamb chops for 3-4 mins on each side, until browned. Season with salt, black pepper and a dash of lemon juice. Add the bacon, garlic and bread and fry until browned. Sprinkle in the thyme.
Spoon the vegetables and chops into serving dishes and garnish with Parmesan shavings, lemon slices and thyme sprigs.

title: potatoes with garlic, chili and feta
directions: Cook the potatoes in boiling, salted water for 15-20 mins until tender. Drain and rinse under cold water until cool enough to handle. Peel the potatoes.
Heat the oil in a large frying pan, add the potatoes and fry for 8-10 mins, turning.
Add the spring onions, chili and garlic to the pan and saute for 4-5 mins with the potatoes, stirring. Season with salt then transfer to a serving bowl. Sprinkle with Feta then serve.

title: summer lentil and chicken soup
directions: Place the chicken in a pan with 4 cups water, the bouquet garni and the brown lentils. Cook over medium heat for about 1 hour. Remove the chicken and the bouquet garni, and add the yellow pepper, green onions and red lentils to the soup. Cook for 10 mins, then add the tomatoes.
Strip the meat from the chicken and chop, then add the meat to the soup. Season with salt and pepper and stir in the chopped parsley.

title: steamed cherry pudding with orange custard
directions: Grease a 5-cup pudding basin or steamer. Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Mix in flour, dried fruit, almonds, cherries and ground almonds. Transfer to prepared pan. Cover with parchment paper then foil. Fold a pleat down the center and secure with butcher's twine. Trim foil and paper, leaving a 3/4 inch overhang.
Transfer to a large saucepan. Add enough water to come halfway up side of pan. Boil, covered, for 3 hours 30 mins, or until a skewer inserted in the center comes out clean.

Meanwhile, to make the candied orange, heat 1/3 cup water with sugar in a small saucepan over low heat, stirring, for 2-3 mins, until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil. Boil, without stirring, for 1 min. Add orange rind and simmer for 5-7 mins, until caramelized. Remove from heat. Use a slotted spoon to transfer rind to parchment paper. Separate strands and set aside for 30 mins until firm.

Meanwhile, to make the orange custard, heat milk, cream and orange zest in a pan over medium heat until just simmering. Remove from heat and let infuse for 10 mins. Whisk together egg yolks and sugar until thick and pale. Whisk warm milk mixture into egg mixture. Return to pan. Stir over low heat for 8-10 mins, until mixture thickens and coats the back of a wooden spoon. Add liqueur. Strain.
Invert pudding onto a serving plate. Top with candied orange. Serve with custard.

title: dark molten puddings
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Place a baking pan on middle shelf to preheat. Line bottoms of six 2/3-cup ramekins or molds with circles of parchment paper.
Beat butter and sugar in a medium bowl with an electric mixer until combined. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in vanilla. Stir in flour, then chocolate. Mix well.
Pour mixture evenly into ramekins. Place ramekins on hot baking pan.
Bake for 14 mins (timing is very important). Invert hot puddings onto serving plates. Gently peel off parchment paper. Serve puddings immediately with berries and ice cream.

title: white chocolate mud cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 300°F. Grease and line bottom and sides of a deep 8-inch square cake pan with 2 layers of parchment paper, extending paper 2 inches above rim.

Place butter, sugar, sour cream and 5 oz white chocolate in a medium saucepan on low heat. Cook and stir for 4-5 mins or until smooth. Remove from heat. Transfer to a large heatproof bowl; cool for 15 mins.

Stir eggs and sifted flours into chocolate mixture. Spoon into prepared pan, smoothing top. Bake for 1 hour 40 mins or until a toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cover pan tightly with foil. Cool cake overnight.

Place remaining 11 oz white chocolate and 1/2 cup cream in a small saucepan on low heat. Cook and stir for 2-3 mins or until smooth. Transfer mixture to a heatproof medium bowl. Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate for 3 hours or until firm. Repeat process using semi-sweet chocolate and remaining 1/4 cup cream.

Reserve two-thirds of the white chocolate mixture to spread on cake. Roll rounded teaspoons of remaining white chocolate mixture into balls to make 10 truffles. Place on a plate. Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate for 30 mins. Repeat process using dark chocolate mixture.

Beat reserved white chocolate mixture in a medium bowl with an electric mixer for 30 seconds or until light and fluffy. Spread over top and sides of cake. Sprinkle tops of white chocolate truffles with silver dragees. Roll dark chocolate truffles in sifted cocoa powder; shake off excess. Arrange truffles on top of cake.

title: caramelized apricots with amaretti butter
directions: Sprinkle the cut side of the apricots with lemon juice. Heat the 2 tbsp of the butter in large non-stick pan and add the apricots. Sprinkle over the sugar and cook gently for 3-4 mins turning occasionally until softened and browned in places.
Add the rest of the butter and the crushed amaretti cookies and simmer for a further few mins until the butter is foaming.
Serve warm with whipped cream, if desired.

title: roasted root veggies
directions: Preheat oven to 425°F. Line a roasting pan with aluminum foil.
Toss vegetables, garlic and thyme with olive oil in prepared pan. Roast, stirring once, for 25 mins, or until vegetables are tender. Smash garlic and remove thyme sprigs. Season.

title: salmon and ricotta salad
directions: Mix salmon, ricotta, chives, sweet chili sauce and lemon juice in a medium bowl. Season to taste.
Add to green salad. Or, spread on crispbread, crusty bread or rolls.

title: grilled veggies and feta
directions: Slice the squash lengthways as thinly as possible. Cut the feta into 3 in x 1 inch pieces and wrap each piece in a slice of squash.
Place the squash wraps on a foil lined grill pan, add the tomatoes and olives and half the thyme. Drizzle with olive oil, season and grill for 15-20 minutes. Serve sprinkled with extra thyme.

title: salmon and scallop tagliatelle
directions: Heat 3 tbsp oil in a saucepan and saute onion and garlic until softened. Sprinkle with flour and cook for 2 mins. Add tomato juice, bring to a boil and simmer for 7 mins. Add anise liqueur, cream, orange juice and zest and simmer for 2 mins. Add vinegar, season and add a pinch of sugar.
Meanwhile, cook pasta in boiling salted water according to package instructions.
Heat 1 tbsp oil in a frying pan and saute salmon for 4 mins, turning. Remove from pan and season with salt. Add scallops and saute for 2 mins on each side, adding thyme when turning. Season.
To serve, drain pasta and toss with sauce. Serve with salmon and scallops, garnished with thyme.

title: clam and chorizo linguine
directions: Soak clams in cold water for 1 hour then drain.
Cook pasta in boiling salted water until al dente then drain. Return to pan.
Meanwhile, heat oil in a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Cook chorizo until crispy. Remove from pan using a slotted spoon.
Add clams to pan, cover and cook for 3 mins, or until clams open. Push clams to 1 side of pan. Add garlic, chilies and tomatoes. Cook for 2 mins, or until fragrant and softened.
Add pasta, basil and extra virgin olive oil. Toss gently to combine. Serve immediately.

title: apple, pear and vanilla sponge cake pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Lightly grease 8 (7 oz) ramekins.
Combine apples and pears. Sprinkle with 2 tbsp sugar and toss to coat. Distribute between ramekins and bake for 35-40 mins, until tender. Let cool. Reduce heat to 350°F.

Meanwhile, in a stand mixer, whip eggs and vanilla until fluffy. Add remaining sugar, 1 tbsp at a time, beating until thick and creamy and sugar is dissolved. Add vanilla extract and mix until combined. Sift flour and spice mix over egg mixture then fold in gently. Distribute between ramekins and bake for 15-20 mins, until a skewer inserted in the center comes out clean.
Serve hot with heavy cream.

title: classic coq au vin
directions: Dust chicken in seasoned flour, shaking off excess. Heat oil in a large heavy-bottomed skillet on medium heat. Brown chicken for 4-5 mins, turning. Remove from pan.
Saute shallots, onion and bacon in same pan for 3-4 mins, until golden. Add garlic; cook 1 min.
Add 2 tbsp flour to pan. Cook, stirring, 1 min. Remove from heat. Add wine and stock, stirring until smooth. Return to heat. Bring to a boil, stirring.
Return chicken to pan with mushrooms, bay leaves and thyme. Reduce heat to low; simmer, covered, 35 mins.
Add carrots and brandy to pan. Simmer, uncovered, a further 10-15 mins, until sauce reduces by one-third. Remove bay leaves. Season to taste. Accompany with vegetables of choice.

title: grilled lime and cinnamon chicken
directions: Combine lime juice, garlic, chopped oregano, cinnamon and chili pepper in a shallow dish and season to taste. Add chicken, turning several times to coat. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours to marinate, turning occasionally.

Preheat the grill to medium-high. Drain chicken, discarding marinade. Grill chicken for 5 mins each side, until just cooked through. Serve with beans and lime wedges. Sprinkle with additional oregano.

title: shrimp cocktail with dill dressing
directions: For the dill dressing, combine mayonnaise, mustard, dill and 1 tbsp cold water. Season.
Distribute lettuce, avocados and mango between serving glasses. Top with shrimp and dressing. Sprinkle with capers and extra dill sprigs. Serve.

title: tiramisu cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Mix the espresso powder with 1 cup boiling water, allow to cool then stir in the liqueur and set aside.

Separate 4 eggs and using an electric hand mixer, beat the whites and vanilla extract with 4 tbsp lukewarm water while slowly adding 2/3 cup of sugar until stiff. Stir in the egg yolks one at a time then fold in the flour and baking powder. Transfer the mixture to a greased 8 inch diameter springform cake pan and bake for 15-20 minutes. Cool on a wire rack and remove from pan.
For the cream, whisk together mascarpone cheese, 2 eggs and 1/3 cup of sugar until thick using an electric hand mixer.

To assemble the cake, cut the cake in half horizontally and place the bottom half on a serving plate. Drizzle with half of the espresso mixture and spread 1/3 of the cream mixture. Place the top layer on the cake and drizzle with remaining espresso. Spread the remaining cream all over the cake and refrigerate for at least 4 hours. Before serving, dust with cocoa powder.

title: rich carbonara tortellini
directions: In a dry non-stick skillet, cook the bacon slices for 5 mins or until crispy, turning once. Remove and keep warm. Add the chopped bacon to the skillet and cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 mins. Remove and set aside.

Add the mushrooms and onion to the skillet with the oil and and bacon fat and cook for approximately 4 mins. Stir through the cream cheese, stock, chopped parsley and chopped bacon. Cook for 1 min to heat through.

Meanwhile cook the tortellini according to the package directions. Drain and stir in the cream cheese sauce. Divide between 4 plates and garnish each serving with a slice of bacon and the parsley leaves.

title: blood orange beer cocktail
directions: Divide the orange juice among 4 glasses. Squeeze 2 lime wedges into each glass and drop in the squeezed peel. Top with beer and garnish with mint.

title: blueberry-pecan loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Lightly coat an 8x4 inch loaf pan with oil.

Sift flour and spice mix together. Add sugar, blueberries, pecans, oat bran and 1 tbsp pumpkin seeds. Whisk together margarine, milk and eggs. Lightly mix into dry ingredients until combined. Transfer mixture to prepared pan, smooth top and sprinkle with remaining seeds. Bake for 50-55 mins, until a skewer comes out clean. Let cool in pan for 5 mins then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.

title: raisin bread and bunny tail twists
directions: Place the flour, sugar and salt in a large mixing bowl and mix. Add 2 of the eggs, the vanilla extract and the butter.

Heat the 1 1/2 cups of milk over a low heat, until lukewarm. Whisk in the yeast until it dissolves. Pour into the flour mixture. Combine with an electric hand whisk fitted with a dough hook, until you have a smooth dough.
Set aside, covered, in a warm place for 45 mins.
Split the dough in half, knead the raisins into one half of the dough. Briefly knead the second piece. Cover both doughs and leave in a warm place for a further 30 mins.
Grease a 10 inch loaf pan. Knead and shape the raisin dough into a 10 inch long loaf and transfer to the pan. Leave in a warm place to rest for 50 mins.

Meanwhile, divide the remaining dough into 8 equal pieces and roll out into long sausage shapes. Cut approximately 1/2 inch from each end and set aside. Fold each piece in half and twist the ends 'over and under'. Place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.

Preheat the oven to 325°F. Use the 1/2 inch ends to cover the little hole that is created by twisting the bread to create a 'bunny tail'. Whisk the remaining egg and the 3 tbsp milk together and brush over the buns (leaving enough for the bread) Sprinkle the 'tails' with the coarse sugar. Set aside, covered, for 10 mins. Then bake for 20 mins.
Brush the bread with the remaining egg and milk mixture and bake for 25 mins. Allow to cool in the pan for 15 mins, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.

title: roast beef with herb crust
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Toss vegetables in 5 tbsp oil, and season. Rub beef with salt and pepper. Heat 2 tbsp oil in a casserole dish and sear beef all over. Place beef on a baking tray and surround with vegetables.

Mix mustard, honey, and half of the chopped herbs. Coat beef with honey mixture. Roast for 35-40 mins. Beef is ready when core temperature is 145°F. Remove from oven and let rest for 10 mins. Serve with vegetables on a platter and garnish with parsley and thyme.

title: semolina pudding with oranges
directions: Slowly bring milk, butter, 2 tbsp sugar and vanilla extract to a boil. Remove from heat and slowly whisk in semolina. Return to heat, bring to a boil, stirring, and cook for 1 min. Remove from heat, cover and set aside for 5 mins.

Meanwhile, mix cornstarch with 1 tbsp orange juice until smooth. Heat remaining juice with liqueur and 2 tbsp sugar, add cornstarch slurry and simmer, stirring, for 1 min until thickened. Fold in orange segments and set aside.

Whisk egg white until stiff then add remaining sugar and a pinch of salt. Whisk egg yolk and cream then add to semolina. Fold in whipped egg white then divide between 4 serving bowls. Garnish with orange segments, syrup and chocolate shavings.

title: halloween ham with potato salad
directions: Boil the potatoes in a pan of lightly salted water for for 15-20 mins until tender. Meanwhile, halve and de-seed the peppers and flatten slightly. Use a small bat-shaped cookie cutter to stamp out 4 bat shapes from each pepper. Set aside.

Whisk together the vinegar, olive oil, honey and mustard and season with salt and freshly ground black pepper. Drain the potatoes. Cool for 10 mins then peel and slice. Place in a bowl and pour over the dressing.
Heat the vegetable oil in a large frying pan and fry the ham steaks over a medium heat for 4-5 mins until cooked through, turning once.
Serve the steaks with potato salad, tomatoes, arugula and the pepper 'bats'. Garnish with scallion tassles.

title: roasted sweet potato and butternut squash soup
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F.
Combine sweet potato, pumpkin and garlic in a baking pan. Toss with 2 tbsp of the oil and season to taste. Bake for 20-30 mins, until tender and golden.
Meanwhile, heat remaining oil in a large saucepan on high heat. Saute onion with spices for 2-3 mins, until tender and aromatic.
Add roasted vegetables to saucepan with stock, 2 cups water and tomatoes. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer for 5-10 mins.
Using an immersion blender, blender or food processor, process soup until smooth. Season to taste and reheat gently. Serve topped with cilantro and a dollop of yogurt.

title: lamb chops with currant couscous and lemon yogurt
directions: Combine oil and cumin in a shallow dish. Season to taste. Add lamb chops, turning to coat in marinade. Let stand for 10 mins to marinate.
For the currant couscous, combine couscous and 1/2 cup boiling water in a medium heatproof bowl. Cover and let stand for 5 mins. Fluff with a fork. Stir in currants, almonds, parsley and sumac.
For the lemon yogurt, combine yogurt, lemon juice and cumin in a small bowl. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Heat an oiled grill pan on high heat or preheat the grill to medium-high. Cook lamb chops for 2-3 mins each side until cooked to desired doneness.
Serve lamb chops with couscous and lemon yogurt. Accompany with salad.

title: corn, pepper and spinach frittatas
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°F. Lightly grease 4 of the cavities of a 6-loaf mini loaf pan (each cavity holds 1 cup).

Heat oil in a medium skillet on medium-high heat. Cook onion, corn and pepper, stirring, for 5 mins or until soft. Add spinach; cook and stir for 1 min or until spinach wilts. Spoon evenly into prepared pan. Top with ricotta and feta. Whisk eggs and milk in a medium bowl. Season. Pour over spinach mixture.
Bake for 25-30 mins or until browned and just set. Let stand for 5 mins. Serve with salad.

title: milk chocolate pots
directions: Place cream and coffee in a small saucepan on medium heat. Bring almost to a boil, stirring to dissolve coffee. Remove from heat. Stir in liqueur and vanilla.
Place chopped chocolate in a medium bowl. Pour cream mixture over and stir until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth.

Whisk in egg yolks and butter, until smooth. Cool for 2-3 mins. Stirring in 3/4 of the chopped candy bar. Spoon mixture evenly into six 1/4-cup ramekins or espresso cups. Refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight.
Top with remaining chopped candy bar and slivered pistachios. Serve with orange wedges, if desired.

title: lime curd tart
directions: For the pastry, process flour, powdered sugar, coconut and butter until crumbly. Add enough iced water (3-4 tbsp) to make ingredients come together. Knead dough gently on floured surface until smooth. Wrap in plastic wrap; refrigerate for 30 mins.

Grease 9-inch round tart pan with removable bottom. Roll pastry between sheets of parchment paper until large enough to line prepared pan. Press pastry into bottom and side of pan; trim edge. Prick bottom with fork. Cover; refrigerate for 30 mins.
Preheat the oven to 400°F. Place tart pan on baking pan. Line pastry with parchment paper and fill with baking beans. Bake for 15 mins; remove paper and beans. Bake for 10 mins; cool.

Meanwhile, for the lime curd, place eggs, yolks, lime peel and juice, sugar and butter in medium saucepan on medium heat. Stir, without boiling, for 15 mins, or until mixture coats the back of a spoon. Strain curd through sieve into medium bowl. Let stand for 10 mins.
Pour lime curd into crust. Refrigerate for 2 hours. Serve tart sprinkled with coconut.

title: poppy seed crumbed chicken wings and red slaw
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.

Place chicken wings in a saucepan along with wine and soy sauce. Add just enough water to cover chicken. Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer for 5 mins. Drain then let chicken cool. Remove skin.
In a large bowl, mix together breadcrumbs, poppy seeds and oil. Season. Dust chicken in flour, shaking off excess. Dip in egg wash then coat in breadcrumb mixture. Bake for 25 mins.
Meanwhile, to make the quick chili sauce, combine chili, tomato juice, vinegar, honey and allspice in a blender. Season then blend until smooth. Set aside.

To make the red slaw, mix onion, cabbage, radicchio and apple in a large bowl. Place rosemary leaves in a mortar and pestle and grind with a pinch of coarse sea salt. Transfer to a small bowl along with vinegar, sugar and oil. Pour over slaw and toss to combine.
Serve chicken wings with red slaw and chili sauce.

title: chicken and corn crepes with cheese sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Grease a small ovenproof dish. For the cheese sauce, melt the butter in a large saucepan over medium heat until foaming. Stir in the flour and chili powder, if using, and cook for 1 min or until the mixture begins to come away from sides of the pan. Gradually add the milk, whisking constantly, until combined. Cook, stirring, for 3-5 mins or until the mixture thickens. Stir in half the cheese.

For the filling, heat the oil in a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Add the chicken, corn, chives and spinach and stir together. Stir in the cheese sauce and heat through. Remove from the heat.

To assemble, divide the filling equally between the crepes. Fold into triangles and transfer to the prepared dish. Sprinkle with the remaining cheese and bake for 10-15 mins, until the cheese melts. Serve with the mixed greens.

title: fruit mousse
directions: In a bowl, mix Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water until dissolved. Chill for 20 mins, or until cold. Add yogurt and whisk until smooth. Distribute between 6 - 8 oz dessert glasses. Cover and chill for 2 hours, or until set.
Top each mousse with fruit to serve.

title: spiced apple cheesecakes
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Lightly grease 8 cups of two 6-cup Texas muffin pans. Line each cup with 2 thin strips of parchment paper, crossing at the bottom.
Using a 2 1/3-inch cutter, cut out 12 rounds from the pastry. Prick in several places with a fork. Place each round in a prepared muffin cup. Bake for 5-10 mins, until golden. Cool.
Beat the cream cheese, sugar and spices in a large bowl with an electric mixer until smooth. Add the yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in the cream until combined.
In a small, clean bowl, beat the egg whites with electric mixer until soft peaks form. Gently fold into the cheesecake mixture.
Top each pastry round with 1 tbsp of filling. Cover with half of the apple slices.
Pour the remaining filling evenly over the apples. Top with the remaining apple slices.
Bake for 20-25 mins, until just firm. Cool in the oven with the door ajar.
Refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight. Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.

title: traffic light cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and honey until light and creamy. Add egg and beat until well combined. Fold in flour and baking soda until just combined. Turn out onto a lightly floured surface and knead until smooth. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill for 15 mins.

Preheat oven to 350°F. Line 2 baking trays with parchment paper. Roll dough out into a 12x8 inch rectangle then cut into 6 - 4x2 inch rectangles. Transfer to prepared trays. Using a 3/4 inch round pastry cutter, cut 3 holes from each rectangle to make the traffic lights.
Fill holes in cookies with crushed candies to resemble traffic lights. Bake for 10 mins, or until golden brown. Let cool on trays.

title: tuna and corn piroshki
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Line a baking tray with parchment paper.
Heat oil in a large frying pan over high heat. Saute leek and zucchini for 4-5 mins, until tender. Transfer to a bowl. Add tuna, creamed corn and cheese. Season.

Place 4 squares of puff pastry onto prepared tray. Distribute filling between centers and brush edges with egg. Top with remaining puff pastry. Press edges together and roll inwards to seal. Brush with egg and bake for 20-25 mins, or until golden brown and puffed.
Serve with salad.

title: pork & asparagus pot pie
directions: Bring a pan of water to a boil and add 1 tsp salt, 2 tsp sugar and the lemon juice. Remove from the heat. Peel the white asparagus then add the asparagus peel and woody trimmings to the water. Cover and leave to stand for 15 mins.

Preheat the oven to 400°F. Remove the asparagus trimmings from the pan and discard. Place the pan back on the heat. Once boiling, add the white asparagus and cook for 2-3 mins. Add the green asparagus and continue to cook for 4-5 mins. Remove the asparagus from the pan and leave to cool. Set the cooking liquid aside.

Heat 1 tbsp oil in a casserole pan, add the pork in batches and saute for 3-4 mins. Remove each batch of pork from the pan and season. Add the mushrooms, potato and onion to the pan and saute for 5-6 mins, stirring. Season lightly then remove from the pan.

Add 1-2 tbsp oil to the pan then stir in the butter. Stir the flour into the hot fat until smooth and cook for 1-2 mins. Gradually stir in the asparagus stock, a little at a time, followed by the cream. Simmer, stirring for 4-5 mins until the sauce thickens. Fold in the asparagus, pork, mushrooms and potato. Season the mixture then transfer to a baking dish.

Roll out the pastry on a lightly floured work surface so that it is slightly larger than the baking dish. Lay the pastry on top then cut off the excess using a sharp knife. Use the scraps to decorate top of the pie.
Make 3 to 4 holes in the pastry lid so that steam can escape. Mix the egg yolk with 3 tbsp water then brush the mixture over the pastry lid. Bake the pie for 20-22 mins until golden then serve.

title: chicken sausages with sage and onion gravy
directions: For the sage and onion gravy, heat oil in a medium saucepan on medium heat. Cook onion, stirring, for 15 mins until caramelized. Add garlic; cook until fragrant. Add flour, cook, stirring, 1 min. Gradually add stock, then sage leaves and cider. Simmer, uncovered, about 10 mins or until gravy is thickened slightly. Season to taste.
Heat oil in a large skillet on medium heat. Cook sausages, turning, for 10 mins or until cooked through.
Microwave mashed potato according to package directions.
Divide sausages among plates. Top with sage and onion gravy. Serve with arugula and mashed potato.

title: roast beef with red wine gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 325°F.

Arrange beef and carrots in a roasting pan. Season. Combine olive oil, 1 tbsp garlic, 1 tbsp chopped thyme and 1 tbsp chopped rosemary then spread over beef. Roast beef and carrots for 1 hour. Add pearl onions and cook for 30 mins, or until a thermometer inserted in the beef reads 145°F for medium-rare, or until cooked to your liking. Transfer to a serving platter, cover and let rest for 15 mins before slicing.

Transfer pan juices to a measuring cup. Skim and discard fat. Heat butter over medium heat. Cook shallot and remaining garlic for 2-3 mins, until softened. Sprinkle flour over top and cook for 1 min, stirring occasionally. Add beef broth, red wine, pan juices and remaining herbs. Simmer for 5 mins, or until slightly thickened. Season. Serve sauce with beef. Garnish with fresh herbs.

title: chunky beef and barley soup
directions: Combine beef, barley, potatoes, carrots, leek, celery, pepper and stock in a pressure cooker.

Cover and lock lid into place. Turn pressure valve to 'cook' position. Place on high heat. When steam begins to escape at a constant rate, reduce heat to low. Cook for 20 mins. Turn off heat. Turn valve to 'steam release' position. When pressure cooker indicator is down, open lid.
Let stand for 5 mins. Season. Stir in parsley. Serve.

title: smoked salmon and rye tea sandwiches
directions: Beat cream cheese, chopped dill and figs together. Season then spread over bread. Lay smoked salmon over top and sandwich bread together. Chill until ready to serve.
Cut into neat squares, discarding crusts. Serve garnished with dill sprigs.

title: raspberry jam and cream sponge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease 2 deep 8 inch cake pans and dust with cornstarch.
Sift cornstarch, cream of tartar, baking soda and a pinch salt into a large bowl. Repeat twice more.
In a separate bowl, whisk eggs, sugar and vanilla together for 10 mins. Carefully fold into dry ingredients until combined. Distribute between prepared pans and bake for 15 mins.
Turn sponge cakes out onto a clean tea towel. When cold, join together with raspberry jam and whipped cream. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: white sauce
directions: In a saucepan, melt the butter. Stir in the flour with a wooden spoon to form a paste. Cook for 2 mins to remove the taste of flour, but don't allow to brown. Gradually add the milk to paste, stirring constantly with a whisk. Once incorporated in the paste, keep adding a bit more milk. Bring to a simmer and cook 5 mins to thicken, whisking constantly. Season with salt and nutmeg.

title: beef casserole with macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Heat the oil in a large skillet on medium-high heat. Add ground beef; cook, stirring with a wooden spoon to break up lumps, for 5 mins or until browned. Stir in the onions and garlic; saute 5 mins. Stir in the tomato paste and saute 30 seconds. Pour in the red wine and 1 1/4 cups water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer for about 10 mins, while stirring. Add the basil and season to taste.

Meanwhile, cook the macaroni in boiling salted water according to the package directions. Melt the butter in a medium saucepan on medium heat. Add the flour and cook, stirring, 30 seconds. Pour in the stock and the milk while stirring. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer for 3-5 mins and season to taste. Stir 1/2 of each cheese into the sauce.
Drain the macaroni and stir it into the sauce. Spoon the beef mixture into a greased baking dish. Cover with the macaroni cheese. Sprinkle with the remaining cheeses.
Bake for 30-40 mins or until golden.

title: apricot ripple lemon frozen yogurt
directions: Put the canister from the ice cream machine into the freezer 18 hours before making the frozen yogurt. Combine yogurt, cream, sugar, 1/3 cup lemon juice and the zest. Turn on machine and slowly pour in the mixture. Leave to churn for 15-20 mins.

Meanwhile, drain apricots and puree. Rinse a 8 x 8 inch freezer-safe pan with cold water and line with plastic wrap. Add apricot puree at very end of churning, so that it streaks through lemon mixture. Scoop frozen yogurt into the pan and freeze at least 2 hours.
Remove frozen yogurt from the freezer and remove from pan with the aid of the plastic wrap. Slice into 2 inch cubes and arrange in cones.

title: happy monkey banana cocktail
directions: Pour the banana liqueur, vodka, whiskey and lemon juice into a tall champagne glass and top with sparkling wine to serve.

title: white gazpacho
directions: Discard crusts from bread. Combine bread in large glass bowl with vinegar and 3 cups water; let stand 15 mins. Whisk in ground almonds and half the chervil.
Meanwhile, place cucumber in a colander. Sprinkle with salt; let stand 15 mins. Rinse cucumber under cold water; drain on paper towels.
Blend or process bread mixture and cream, in batches, until smooth. Return soup mixture to same bowl; stir in cucumber.
Season soup to taste. Divide soup among serving bowls. Drizzle with oil and sprinkle with remaining chervil.

title: egg and coleslaw double-decker sandwich
directions: Combine eggs and 2 tbsp aioli in medium bowl; season to taste.
Combine coleslaw mix and remaining aioli in another medium bowl; season to taste.

Spread 4 bread slices with coleslaw mixture; top with 4 bread slices. Spread bread with egg mixture, then top with remaining bread. Cut sandwiches in half. Push a cocktail stick into each sandwich to hold them together.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Cook the cauliflower in salted, boiling water for 3-4 mins then add the broccoli and carrots and cook for another 3-4 mins. Drain thoroughly.
Beat the eggs and mix in 1/2 cup cheese, the milk and nutmeg and season with salt and pepper.

Roll out the pastry on a lightly floured work surface to make a 12 inch-diameter circle. Lightly grease a 10 inch-diameter tart pan with removable bottom. Line the pan with the pastry and trim any excess. Arrange the vegetables and tomatoes inside the pastry shell, then pour over the egg mixture. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.

Bake the tart for 50 mins-1 hour, until the filling has just set and the pastry is golden. Check halfway through cooking time, and cover with aluminum foil if the edges become too dark. Serve warm or cold.

title: chutney and mustard meatloaf
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Grease a foil-lined 8 x 4 inch loaf pan
Heat oil in a skillet on medium heat. Add the onion and saute for 4-5 mins, until tender. Cool slightly.
Place ground pork, breadcrumbs, eggs, bacon, parsley, chutney, mustard and onion in a large bowl and season to taste. Mix until well combined. Spoon into prepared pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until golden brown and cooked through. Let stand for 5 mins. Drain off any drippings, then remove meatloaf from pan. Serve sliced with salad and chutney.

title: tomato and basil crackers
directions: Sift flour into a large bowl. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse breadcrumbs. Stir in basil, tomato puree and pepper. Add 1-2 tbsp ice water and mix until mixture just comes together. Turn out onto a lightly floured work surface and knead until smooth. Cover and refrigerate for 30 mins.
Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease 2 baking trays.

Roll dough out on a floured work surface until 1/8 inch thick. Prick all over with a fork and cut into 1 1/2 inch squares. Place about 1/3 inch apart on trays. Brush with egg white and sprinkle with salt. Bake for 15 mins, or until light golden brown. Let cool on trays.

title: christmas pudding
directions: Combine the fruit and rum or brandy in a large bowl. Cover and let stand overnight.
Grease a 6-cup pudding basin or two 3-cup pudding basins. Line the bottom of the basin with a circle of parchment paper.

Beat the butter, sugar and peels in a large bowl with an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in the fruit. Sift the flour, baking powder, spices and 1/2 tsp salt into a medium bowl. Fold into the fruit mixture. Fold in the breadcrumbs.

Spoon the mixture into basin. Cover with a circle of parchment paper, then more parchment paper and foil, folding it over the edge. Secure with string, leaving a loop on opposite sides of the basins to lift the pudding out when it is cooked.
Place a trivet or heatproof saucer in the bottom of a large saucepan half filled with boiling water. Lower in the pudding, making sure the water comes 2/3 up the sides of basin.

Cover and steam for 5 hours on low heat, making sure that the water is constantly bubbling. Add boiling water as necessary to maintain the water level. Remove the basin from pan, cool completely and store in the fridge until Christmas Day.

To serve, steam the pudding for 2 hours using the same method, or microwave for 5-8 mins, depending on the size. Cut into wedges and serve with custard, ice cream, brandy butter or rum sauce, as desired.

title: dessert pizza with caramelized apples
directions: Put the yeast in a small bowl with 2 tablespoons of sugar and 1/4 cup water and mix until dissolved. Meanwhile, gently melt 2 tbsp of the butter in a pan then add the milk. In a large bowl, mix the flour, egg, vanilla extract, 1 tsp sugar, and a pinch of salt. Slowly add the warm milk, then the yeast, mixing to create a smooth dough (you can use a food processor with a dough hook for this). Cover the dough and let rise in a warm place for about 30 mins.

Meanwhile, drizzle the sliced apples with lemon juice. Heat 2 tbsp butter in a non-stick pan and sprinkle with 1/4 cup of sugar. After 1-2 mins the mixture will begin to caramelize. Toss the apples in the caramel, then remove from the pan and allow to cool.

Preheat oven to 400°F. Lift the dough onto a floured work surface, knead briefly, then roll out into an 11 inch circle. Lift the dough onto a baking sheet lined with baking paper. Spread the cranberry sauce over the dough, then distribute the apple slices on top. Let rest for 5 mins, then bake for 20-25 mins.

Meanwhile toast the almonds in a pan until they are golden and fragrant. In a bowl, mix the sour cream with the cinnamon and a 1 tsp of sugar. Remove the pizza from the oven and sprinkle the almonds over the top, then dust with powdered sugar. Serve hot with the cinnamon cream on the side.

title: ginger, ricotta and almond meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 300°F. Line 2 baking trays with parchment paper.

Whip egg whites to stiff peaks. Gradually whisk in sugar, 1 tbsp at a time, until mixture is thick and glossy. Fold in ground almonds. Transfer to a piping bag fitted with a plain tip and pipe 1 1/2 inch rounds onto prepared trays. Sprinkle with chopped almonds. Bake for 30 mins then turn off oven and let meringues cool in oven with door ajar.
Meanwhile, combine ricotta, honey and ginger. Sandwich meringues together with ricotta mixture. Serve.

title: cheese ravioli with arugula
directions: Cook pasta in a large saucepan of boiling salted water according to package directions. Drain and return to pan.

Meanwhile, heat oil in a medium skillet on high heat. Add onion and garlic and saute 2-3 mins, until tender. Stir in cream; simmer 3-4 mins, until mixture thickens. Remove from heat. Stir in cheeses and 1/2 the walnuts.
Pour sauce over ravioli; toss to coat. Serve immediately, topped with remaining walnuts and arugula leaves.

title: lime, vanilla and star anise fruit salad
directions: Place granulated sugar and 1/2 cup water in small saucepan on low heat. Stir until sugar has dissolved. Add star anise and vanilla bean paste. Increase heat to high and boil for 2 mins. Remove from heat. Add lime peel and juice. Cover and set aside to cool.
Place papaya, strawberries, pineapple, melon and mint in a bowl. Pour cooled syrup over top and toss to coat.
Stir brown sugar into yogurt; serve over fruit salad.

title: slow-cooked winter ragu
directions: Preheat oven to 300°F. Heat 2 tbsp oil in a large Dutch oven over high heat. Working in batches, sear rabbit pieces for 5 mins, until golden brown. Set aside.

Add remaining oil to pan and reduce heat to medium. Cook onion for 5 mins, until softened. Add pancetta, carrot and garlic. Cook for 5 mins, until starting to brown. Return rabbit to pan along with peppercorns and bouquet garni. Add wine, stock, tomatoes and tomato paste. Cover and bring to a boil. Transfer to the oven and bake for 1 hour, until rabbit is cooked through and tender.
Remove rabbit from sauce. Let cool slightly then remove meat from bones.
Meanwhile, heat rabbit sauce over medium heat for 3-4 mins, until reduced slightly. Return rabbit meat to sauce and cook for 1 min, until heated through. Sprinkle with Parmesan and parsley.

title: taco fiesta
directions: For the guacamole, place avocado in a medium bowl. Mash well with lime juice and season to taste.
For the salsa, combine tomato, onion, cilantro, lime juice and chili pepper in a medium bowl. Season to taste.
Drizzle 1 tbsp of the oil over beef and sprinkle with 1/2 of the taco seasoning. Repeat with fish in a second bowl, using remaining oil and seasoning.
Preheat the grill to medium-high. Grill beef 3-4 mins each side for medium, or until cooked to desired doneness. Let stand, loosely covered with foil, for 5 mins.
Grill or cook fish in heated skillet 1-2 mins each side, until golden and just cooked through.
Meanwhile, heat taco shells according to package directions.
Thinly slice beef. Arrange beef and fish on platter with salsa, guacamole and taco shells. Accompany with lettuce, cheese, sour cream and tabasco sauce for everyone to build their own favorite taco.

title: lamb kebabs with herb couscous
directions: In a large bowl, combine lamb, wine, mustard, lemon juice, thyme, chili sauce and garlic. Season to taste. Cover and let marinate for 30 mins.
Thread lamb, tomatoes and onion onto soaked wooden skewers. Preheat grill. Grill kebabs, turning, for 10-12 mins, or until cooked to your liking.
For the herbed couscous, bring stock and 1/2 cup water to a boil. Pour over couscous, cover and let stand for 5 mins. Fluff with a fork. Add chickpeas and parsley. Season to taste. Serve with kebabs.

title: broccoli orecchiette
directions: Cook the broccoli in boiling salted water for 2 mins. Drain and refresh in cold water. Cook the pasta according to package instructions. Drain.

Heat 3 tbsp oil in a large frying pan and saute the garlic and chilis for 1 min. Add the broccoli and anchovies and saute for 2 mins. Season with salt and black pepper. Add the pasta and toss well. Heat again and drizzle with 3 tbsp oil.

title: pecan danish
directions: Cut lard into bread mix until mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs. Add sugar. Mix together egg yolks and milk then mix into dry ingredients until smooth. Knead for 5 mins on a lightly floured work surface, until smooth. Transfer to a lightly greased bowl, cover and let rise in a warm place for 10 mins.

Turn dough out onto a lightly floured work surface and knead for 5 mins, until smooth. Shape into 3 - 5 inch logs. Braid together, using water to stick ends together. Place on a greased baking sheet and sprinkle with 1/2 cup pecans. Lightly cover with a sheet of oiled plastic wrap and leave in a warm place for 30 mins to rise.
Preheat oven to 425°F. Bake danish for 15 mins, until golden brown. Brush syrup over top, sprinkle with remaining nuts and bake for 5 mins. Drizzle with icing. Serve warm or cold.

title: apricots and raspberries with oat brittle and lime yogurt
directions: Caramelize the sugar by heating it in a dry pan until golden in color. Add the oats and mix so the oats are coated with the caramelized sugar. Remove from the pan and spread into a thin layer on a sheet of aluminium foil and allow to cool.
Mix the raspberries and apricots with 3 tablespoons of lime juice and the honey and leave to marinate for about 5 mins.
Meanwhile, in another bowl mix the yogurt with the rest of the lime juice, a teaspoon of the zest and the powdered sugar.

To serve, put the apricot and raspberries in individual bowls and crumble the oat brittle on top. Drizzle over a little of the lime yogurt and serve with the rest of the yogurt on the side. Garnish with the remaining zest.

title: coconut cherry cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Line 8 recesses of a 12-cup muffin pan with paper liners.

Beat butter, coconut extract, sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing well between each addition. Gently fold in flour alternately with milk until just combined. Distribute between paper liners and bake for 20 mins, or until a skewer inserted in the center comes out clean. Let cupcakes cool in pan for 5 mins then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.
Meanwhile, to make the cream cheese frosting, beat butter and cream cheese until light and fluffy. Gradually beat in powdered sugar. Transfer to a large piping bag fitted with a large fluted tip.
Pipe large swirls of frosting onto each cupcake. Sprinkle lightly with desiccated coconut and top with a maraschino cherry.

title: lemongrass beef with rice noodles
directions: In a food processor, combine onion, honey, lemongrass and garlic. Process to a rough paste. Add fish sauce and white pepper to taste. Coat beef, cover and marinate for 1 hour.
Working in 2 batches, heat 1 tbsp peanut oil in a large wok or frying pan over high heat. Stir-fry beef for 1-2 mins, until browned. Distribute over cooked rice noodles to serve.
Serve with cucumber spears and lime wedges.

title: cauliflower soup with meatballs
directions: Bring the broth to a boil in a large saucepan. Add the cauliflower and cook for 12-15 mins until tender. Remove using a slotted spoon and set aside. Add the potatoes to the broth and cook for 18-20 mins until tender.

Meanwhile, place the ground beef, breadcrumbs, ketchup and mustard in a bowl and season with salt and pepper. Knead the mixture together until smooth. With slightly wet hands, form the mixture into 16 meatballs. Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium heat, add the meatballs and cook for 6-8 mins, turning, until cooked through.

Return half the cauliflower to the saucepan. Transfer the remaining cauliflower to a blender or food processor and puree until smooth, then add to the saucepan. Bring to a simmer, then stir in the cream cheese until smooth. Stir in the remaining cauliflower, the curry powder and salt and pepper to taste; warm through. Divide the soup among four bowls, top with the meatballs and chives and serve.

title: vegetarian nachos
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F.

Heat olive oil in a frying pan over medium heat. Sweat onion and garlic, stirring, for 5 mins, or until onion softens. Add tomatoes and kidney beans. Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer for 15 mins, stirring constantly, until thickened slightly.
Arrange tortilla chips on a large ovenproof plate. Spoon bean mixture over top then sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 10 mins, or until cheese is melted. Serve topped with sour cream and fresh cilantro.

title: swiss chard spanakopita rolls
directions: Place chard in a saucepan over moderate heat. Cover; cook, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes, or until just wilted. Drain.
When cool enough to handle, squeeze excess liquid from chard; chop finely.
Combine cheeses, herbs, onion and rice in a bowl. Add chard; mix well. Season.
Preheat oven to hot, 400°F. Line a baking sheet with parchment.
Lightly spray top of 3 pastry sheets with oil. Stack together. Fold stack in half crossways.
Spoon one-quarter chard mixture along long edge of pastry, leaving a 2-inch border. Fold in sides; roll up firmly to enclose filling. Place, seam side down, on prepared tray. Spray lightly with oil.
Repeat, using remaining pastry and filling, to make 4 rolls. Sprinkle rolls with sesame seeds.
Bake 20 minutes, or until golden and crisp. Serve warm.

title: chicken, lemon and tomato risotto
directions: Bring stock and 3 cups water to a boil in a medium saucepan on high heat. Add lemon peel and juice. Reduce heat to low. Cover and keep hot.
Melt butter in a large saucepan on medium heat. Saute onion for 2-3 mins until tender. Add rice and cook, stirring, 1 min.

Reduce heat to medium-low. Add a ladleful of hot stock to rice mixture; stir constantly until liquid is absorbed. Continue to add stock, 1 ladleful at a time, stirring constantly until liquid is absorbed before adding more (this will take about 35 mins or until rice is tender but firm to the bite).

Meanwhile, heat oil in a large skillet on high heat. Cook chicken for 3-4 mins until cooked through. Remove pan from heat. Stir in tomatoes, Parmesan cheese and chives. Season to taste. Stir into risotto. Serve with additional Parmesan cheese.

title: crustless broccoli quiche
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Spray a 9-inch quiche dish or pie plate with no sick cooking spray. Dust with the breadcrumbs.
Arrange broccoli, pepper, ham and cheese in dish. Whisk eggs, milk and mustard in a medium bowl. Season to taste. Pour over vegetable mixture.
Bake for 35-40 mins, until firm and golden. Cut into wedges and serve with salad.

title: egg salad with green chili
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, mustard, chili peppers and onions in small bowl.
Pour over eggs; toss lightly. Season with salt and pepper.

title: peking duck lettuce wraps
directions: In a wok or large frying pan, heat oil until very hot. Stir-fry mushrooms, shallot and garlic for 1 min. Add duck meat, water chestnuts and carrot. Stir-fry for 1 min. Deglaze with wine. Add hoisin sauce and soy sauce. Bring to a simmer and cook for 1-2 mins, until sauce thickens. Remove from heat. Add snow peas and bean sprouts. Toss to combine.
Serve in lettuce cups.

title: creamy mushroom and potato soup
directions: Heat 1 tbsp of the butter in a medium saucepan and fry the scallions and potatoes for 6-7 mins. Pour in the stock and bring to a boil, then cover and simmer for 10-15 mins until the potatoes are tender.
Meanwhile, heat the rest of the butter in a large frying pan and fry the mushrooms over high heat for 4-5 mins until tender. Season to taste and set aside.

Puree the soup with an immersion blender, then add the mushrooms and simmer over low heat for 2 mins. Stir in half the cream and simmer for 1-2 mins. Season to taste. Serve in bowls topped with the rest of the cream and chopped scallions and garnished with borage flowers, if desired.

title: chicken with cashews and ginger
directions: Cook green beans in a large saucepan of boiling salted water for 2 mins or until just tender. Drain well. Refresh under cold running water.

Heat a wok or large skillet on medium heat. Add half the oil; swirl to coat surface. Stir-fry cashews for 2 mins or until toasted. Transfer to a plate. Add remaining oil to wok; stir-fry chicken, in batches, for 2 mins or until browned. Transfer to a plate.

Add onion, pepper and beans to wok; stir-fry for 2 mins or until just tender. Return chicken to wok. Add ginger, sambal oelek and lemon juice; stir-fry for 2 mins or until chicken is cooked through. Remove from heat.
Add cashews, chili pepper and cilantro; toss to combine. Serve with rice and lime wedges

title: chocolate pecan cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Grease 2 baking pans and line with parchment paper. Process pecan pieces until they are ground finely.

Beat butter, sugar, vanilla and ground pecans in large bowl with electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add egg; beat until combined. Sift flour and cornstarch; stir in cookie dough. Stir in chopped chocolate.
Roll rounded tablespoons of mixture into balls. Place 2 inches apart on prepared pans; flatten slightly. Top with whole pecans.
Bake for about 20 mins. Cool in pan 2 mins. Remove from pan; completely on wire rack. Drizzle with melted chocolate.

title: honeycomb cream cupcakes
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Line a 6-cup Texas muffin pan or 12-cup standard muffin pan with paper liners.

Sift dry ingredients into large bowl. Add butter, egg, buttermilk and syrup; beat with electric mixer on low speed until combined. Increase speed to medium; beat until light and fluffy. Stir in chocolate. Divide mixture among muffin cups; smooth top.
Bake large cupcakes about 40 mins, small cupcakes about 30 mins. Cool in pan 5 mins. Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.
Spread cupcakes with whipped cream; top with candy bar.

title: individual spicy salami pan pizzas
directions: Place the flour, sugar, salt and yeast in a bowl and add the oil and 1 1/4 cups lukewarm water. Knead with the dough hook of a mixer for 5 mins, adding more water if necessary. Cover and allow to rest in a warm place for 2 hours.

Preheat the oven to 425°F. Grease an 8 inch diameter baking pan. Cut the dough into 4 pieces and press one into the bottom of the pan, forming a slightly raised edge. Spread with 1/4 of the pizza sauce and sprinkle with 1/4 of the salami, pepperoncini, rosemary, mozzarella and Gouda.

Cook over a high heat on the stove for 2 mins, then transfer to the oven and bake for 10 mins, until the cheese is golden and bubbling. Remove from the pan and repeat 3 times with the remaining ingredients.

title: chickpea and vegetable tagine
directions: Heat oil in large deep skillet on medium-high heat. Cook onion and garlic, stirring, until onion softens. Add spices, chili pepper and eggplant; cook, stirring, until fragrant.

Add pumpkin, undrained tomatoes, stock, 2 cups water and chickpeas; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer, covered, 10 mins. Add zucchini; simmer, covered, 5 mins or until vegetables are tender.

Meanwhile, for the couscous, place stock, 1 cup water and butter in large saucepan; bring to a boil. Stir in couscous. Remove from heat. Let stand, covered, about 5 mins or until liquid is absorbed, fluffing with fork occasionally.
Stir cilantro and lemon juice into vegetable mixture. Serve with couscous.

title: croque monsieur
directions: Spread mustard over bread. Top 2 slices with ham and cheese. Top with remaining bread.
In a large frying pan, melt butter over medium heat. Cook sandwiches for 2-3 mins per side, or until golden brown and cheese is melted. Serve immediately.

title: dundee cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 300°F. Line a deep 8-inch cake pan with 3 layers of parchment paper, bringing paper 2 inches above edge of pan.

Beat butter, sugar, eggs, sifted flours and spice, and milk in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed for 3 mins, or until mixture changes color slightly. Stir in fruit and nuts, mixing well. Spread into prepared pan. Decorate top with additional cherries and nuts.
Bake for 3 hours, or until a skewer comes out clean. Brush hot cake with brandy. Cover with foil. Cool in pan on a wire rack.

title: tomato apricot cocktail
directions: Place the apricot halves and apricot juice in a blender and puree until smooth.
Pour into a cocktail glass with ice, add tomato juice and lemon juice and top with sparkling water.

title: individual tiramisu
directions: Using the coffee and boiling water, prepare the coffee in a French press. Pour into a medium bowl and stir in 2/3 cup marsala.
Beat the egg yolks and 1/4 cup sugar in a small bowl with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Beat the mascarpone and the rest of the marsala in a large bowl with a wooden spoon until well combined. Gently fold in the egg yolk mixture.
Beat egg whites and the remaining sugar in a clean, small bowl with an electric mixer until soft peaks form. Gently fold egg white mixture into the mascarpone mixture.

Dip the ladyfingers, a couple at a time, into the coffee mixture until they start to soften, then arrange them around the sides of twelve 10-oz. desert glasses. Spoon any left-over coffee mixture over the top of the biscuits.
Divide the mascarpone mixture among the glasses then cover and refrigerate overnight. Just before serving, dust the tops with sifted cocoa.

title: gazpacho
directions: In a large bowl, combine vegetables and garlic. Add bread, olive oil, vinegar, chili and sugar. Cover with 1/2 cup water. Season. Cover with plastic wrap and chill for at least 3 hours.
Transfer mixture to a food processor or blender along with 3.5 oz ice cubes and process until smooth. Strain then pour into serving glasses.
Serve topped with a little tomato, pepper, onion and mini croutons.

title: baby artichoke salad
directions: To prepare the artichokes, cut off stems and remove any fibrous material. Chop off about a 1/3 of the way down from the top with a sharp knife. Cut off tough outer leaves and clip any remaining leaves with a pair of scissors. Add lemon juice to a pot of boiling, salted water then immediately add artichokes. Cook for 15 mins, until leaves begin to come away. Drain. Cut into wide strips.
Heat 2 tbsp oil in a saucepan. Saute artichokes for about 3 mins. Season. Add green onions, garlic and chopped thyme. Cook for 1 min. Remove artichokes from pan and let cool.
Meanwhile, combine mixed greens, basil and mozzarella. Whisk together vinegar, remaining olive oil, honey and mustard. Season then toss with salad. Arrange artichokes over top.

title: hot cross bun pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°F. Lightly grease a 6-cup ovenproof dish.
In a medium skillet, combine brown sugar and 1 tbsp water. Heat on low, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Add pear slices and simmer, uncovered, for 3-5 mins, until just tender, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat.
In a medium saucepan, bring milk, cream and vanilla bean and seeds to boiling point. Remove from heat. Cover and set aside for 5 mins. Discard vanilla bean.
Arrange buns and pears in alternate layers in prepared dish. In a large bowl, whisk eggs, sugar, cinnamon, and nutmeg together. Gradually whisk in warm cream mixture.
Strain egg mixture carefully over buns and pears. Place dish in large roasting pan and pour enough boiling water into the pan to come halfway up the sides of the dish.
Bake for 55-60 mins, until set. Serve with ice cream or cream.

title: double chocolate raspberry brownie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease and line a 10x6 inch rimmed baking pan with parchment paper. Melt dark chocolate and butter over low heat. Remove from heat. Whisk in eggs and sugar until well combined. Fold in flour then white chocolate and raspberries.
Transfer to prepared pan and bake for around 20 mins. Edges will come away from sides of pan slightly but center will still be fudgy. Let cool in pan completely then cut into 16 pieces. Serve.

title: southwest cheesy bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Lightly grease and line 2 baking trays.

Spread refried beans over 1 sheet of puff pastry. Sprinkle with 3 oz cheese and parsley. Top with remaining sheet of dough and press down to adhere. Brush with egg then cut into 8 even strips. Holding each end, twist into spirals. Arrange, 2 inches apart, on prepared trays. Sprinkle with sesame seeds and remaining cheese. Bake for 15-20 mins, until puffed and golden brown. Let cool slightly.
Serve with salsa.

title: caramelized onion and polenta cake
directions: Grease a 9-inch square baking dish with oil.
Heat oil in a large skillet on low heat. Cook onion for 15 mins, until soft. Add sugar and vinegar. Cook, stirring, for 5 mins, until caramelized. Remove from heat. Stir in cheese.

Bring 6 cups salted water to a boil in a medium saucepan on high heat. Reduce heat to medium. Gradually add polenta in a thin, steady stream, whisking constantly, until smooth. Reduce heat to low. Cook, stirring, for 5-10 mins, until polenta comes away cleanly from side of pan. Stir in 1/2 each of the butter and Parmesan cheese.

Preheat the broiler on high. Pour 1/2 of polenta into prepared dish. Spread with onion mixture then remaining polenta. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese and dot with remaining butter. Broil for 5 mins, until golden. Cut into squares. Serve with salad.

title: passionfruit cream sponge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease and line base and sides of two 8 inch round cake pans with parchment paper.
Beat egg whites until firm peaks form. Add sugar, 1 tbsp at a time, beating constantly, until thick and glossy.
Using a large metal spoon, gently fold in yolks, then flour and 1/4 cup boiling water, until just combined.
Divide mixture between prepared pans and bake for 20-25 mins, until cakes spring back when touched. Turn out on to a wire rack lined with a tea towel to cool.

To make the passionfruit cream, whip cream and sugar until soft peaks form. Fold in passionfruit pulp. To assemble, spread cream over top of 1 cake. Top with remaining cake. Dust with powdered sugar, slice and serve.

title: german christmas buns
directions: Mix the rum and raisins/sultanas and allow to soak. Place the flour in a mixing bowl and make a well in the centre. In a saucepan, heat half of the milk until lukewarm, add the yeast and allow to dissolve. Pour into the well along with 2 tbsp sugar and brush over a little flour. Cover and allow to rest in a warm place for 30 mins.

In a saucepan, melt 1 3/4 stick butter and stir in the remaining milk. Add to the flour mixture along with the vanilla extract, lemon zest, ground almonds, remaining sugar and a pinch of salt. Knead with the dough hook of a mixer. Add the raisins and 2/3 cup chopped almonds and knead with your hands. Cover and allow to rest in a warm place for 1 hour.

Preheat the oven to 400°F. Line 3 baking sheets with parchment paper. Divide the dough into about 65 pieces and shape into ovals. Place on the baking sheets and flatten with a spoon. Melt the remaining butter and spread half of it over the biscuits. Sprinkle over the remaining chopped almonds and press lightly. Bake one sheet at a time for 12 mins each, until golden brown.
Spread the the remaining melted butter over the hot biscuits. Dust with the icing sugar and allow to cool.

title: bacon and mushroom wheatberry stew
directions: Rinse the wheatberries then place in a bowl filled with 1 cup of cold water overnight.

Heat the oil in a saucepan, add the onion and garlic and saute for 2-3 mins. Stir in the tomato puree and saute for a further 1-2 mins. Add the wheatberries and the soaking water to the pan. Bring to the boil and stir in the porcini powder. Cover and simmer for 30-40 mins.

Heat a non-stick frying pan and add the ham. Fry for 2-3 minutes then remove from the pan. Add the mushrooms to the fat in the pan and fry for 4-5 mins. Stir the carrots and leek into the wheatberry pan and continue to cook for a further 10 mins. Once cooked, fold the ham, Parmesan and mushrooms into the wheatberries and season. Divide between 4 bowls then serve.

title: mix and match bruschetta
directions: Preheat oven to 300°F. Line a baking sheet with parchment.
For the tomatoes: Arrange tomatoes on baking sheet. Drizzle with oil and balsamic. Season to taste. Bake 10-15 minutes, until tender.
For the lemon mushrooms: Cut mushrooms into wafer-thin slices. Place in a small bowl with oil and juice. Season to taste. Marinate at least 10 minutes. Toss with chopped parsley just before serving.

For the crostini: Rub one side of each bread slice with cut garlic clove. Then brush both sides with oil and arrange on baking sheet. Bake 6-8 minutes, turning halfway through, until golden and crisp.
To serve, top crostini with either tomatoes and feta or mushrooms and parsley.

title: cappuccino cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Line a 12-cup muffin pan with paper liners. Beat pastry flour, baking powder, butter, brown sugar, eggs, milk, coffee liqueur and instant whipped cream until creamy. Divide between paper liners and bake for 12-15 mins. Cool in pan for 10 mins then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.

Meanwhile, beat cream cheese and vanilla until smooth. Gradually add powdered sugar. Transfer to a piping bag fitted with a 1/3 inch plain tip and pipe icing onto cooled cakes. Sprinkle with chocolate curls.

title: chicken meatballs with vegetable mash
directions: Preheat the oven to 200°F. Mix the chicken, apricot, 1 onion, the garlic, parsley, chili and quark (or whipped cream cheese or mascarpone) together and season.
